comment: I used to be in house keeping at a hotel a lot of rich people stayed at....my very first day. I walk in to a run that a professional basketball ball player was staying in. I had the door propped open with the vacuum cleaner as, that was the hotel's rule. It enough of a mess for 5 people. I get to the bathroom and there was a huge log of human shit on the floor. I yelled at the top of my lungs, which got me in trouble because the hotel had a policy of keeping famous people's nasty habits hush hush.  But I yelled for my supervising trainer aka a person who has worked in hotel house keeping longer than me. She ran in and yelled "it's  not a body is it?" I was in shock by the fact someone walk about a foot in to their bathroom then gave up on making it to the toilet, so they shat on the floor. So I said "I think I can handle a corpse. You call the police if that happens. There is a log of shit on the ground the size of my arm! " she went to call the head of house keeping because we needed special  gloves to clean up said log. I had just started and I said that 2 things were going to happen  here. I am not looking to get hepatitis  for a crappy paying job. So I need a raise. I need to be able to refuse cleaning rooms with human excitement on the floor, walls, bed, what ever because the hotel might value that basketball player's fame  but I don't.  He's am adult man that took a dump on the floor. They might not reprimand him for that but I will. I will stand outside the hotel and screen that he took a giant shit on the floor. I was told "kid, celebrities do this kind of thing all the time." Which they don't. I cleaned other famous people 's rooms. Famous magician, never shat on the floor. Famous singer, never shat on the floor. Guy in charge of a movie studio,  didn't shit on the floor. I really feel for the maid that found that. I have been there sister! We could start a support group.

comment:
It's not the first time....
I used to hang out at "the wreck" - a series of hills in a wooded area that kids bikes over the years had trampled the weeds away making it perfect for bike thrills & tricks.
One Saturday, we were all shocked that the snobby girl turned up without her horse, or bike.
There were a few girls (regulars) mostly boys. She was instantly upset for not being Center of attention. 
She quickly removed her clothes, and was wearing a ballet leotard underneath. 
It was pale blue, with a cute V neck, and had a 4 inch, pleated 'skirt' below waist that was high at hips, and curved down front & back, but was absolutely useless in hiding anything, or looking even remotely appropriate in current setting.
She opened up the lower part below the skirt by popping 3 stud buttons, squatted down (in front of everyone) and dropped her guts right in the middle of one of the tracks between 2 of the hills.
Us girls were disgusted and started walking away, but the boys cheered, laughed, and started following her!
One boy picked it up on the end of a big stick and was threatening to touch the other boys with it.
More laughter, then one of the boys said "hey, where'd she go"!? 
She had made her mark, caused a disturbance, reasserted herself as Alpha attention seeker, and left satisfied. 
She left her clothes behind!
The boy carrying the stick smeared it all over her skirt, then carefully laid her blouse on top and stamped the 2 articles of abandoned clothing together!
